1772472888638683	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEw-Ac		item.create	bn-2uef	{"description":"In handle_triage and handle_question, when escalation is detected the code calls handle_dev(&reason, None) without first creating a bone. handle_dev just spawns the dev-loop binary, which then runs bn next, finds nothing, and either dispatches a worker that also finds nothing or does nothing itself. Fix: create the bone first (like handle_mission does), post the bone ID to channel, then call handle_dev with the bone_id. Both escalation paths need the fix: handle_triage (line ~1190) and handle_question (line ~868).","kind":"bug","title":"Triage/question escalation doesn't create bone before spawning dev-loop"}	blake3:XEMK1MLqk5S5Ut61-kSydc719Gqa07HwCXUVjob22_I
1772472888843769	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEw-Qc		item.create	bn-32k3	{"description":"build_triage_prompt tells haiku to 'acknowledge it' when it sees a work request. Haiku takes this seriously and posts confident, detailed technical responses ('Will fix by removing the spaces') before any bone exists or work is dispatched. The channel gets a promise that nothing backs up. Fix: replace 'acknowledge it' with a minimal instruction — just confirm receipt, no promises, no technical analysis. Something like 'Post a brief one-line acknowledgment (do not make promises or describe a solution)'.","kind":"bug","title":"Triage prompt over-commits haiku before bone exists"}	blake3:yKUE8aECqn8-T7U7AyUf2xT3kZciJGTzUWt9A0YuxG0
1772472889024941	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEw-gc		item.create	bn-zkq9	{"description":"When worker-loop exits because bn next returns nothing after N checks, it just logs internally and signs off without posting to the channel. Users who asked questions like '@bones-dev/0 did you file the bone or make the fix?' get no response. Fix: post a message to the project channel before exiting when no work was found, e.g. 'No ready bones found after N checks — nothing to work on. Check bn triage for status.'","kind":"bug","title":"Worker signs off silently when no work found"}	blake3:r1ySlAvHSxL_A2eykMgow-0pOa_0F4vWcLZV188iNxU
