1772643022489906	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwjAg		item.create	bn-3jgn	{"description":"Change package name, binary name, and lib name in Cargo.toml from 'botbox' to 'edict'. This is the foundational rename — until this is done, the binary is still invoked as 'botbox' and none of the edict migration code runs under its new name. Also update any references to the crate name in source (extern crate, use botbox::, etc.).","kind":"task","title":"rename: Cargo.toml binary and crate from botbox to edict"}	blake3:BgrtdG6MhrAKQ_VqurGOwA1UD3Kg3XToj585G3SlObw
1772643022667573	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwjQg		item.create	bn-2exa	{"description":"Rename all BOTBOX_* environment variables to EDICT_*: BOTBOX_MISSION, BOTBOX_PROJECT, BOTBOX_BONE, BOTBOX_WORKSPACE, BOTBOX_SIBLINGS, BOTBOX_FILE_HINTS, BOTBOX_MISSION_OUTCOME, BOTBOX_AGENT, BOTBOX_HOOKS_EXTENSION, BOTBOX_BEAD. These are set and read in dev_loop/prompt.rs and passed into spawned Claude agent processes. The spawned agents read them by name, so both sides must change together.","kind":"task","title":"rename: BOTBOX_* env vars to EDICT_*"}	blake3:AxWJY92_dfjHx5wqmanhQBs6IxJltZkac-zSCge4rDE
1772643022846616	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwjgg		item.create	bn-2nxp	{"description":"Update all embedded doc templates in src/templates/docs/ that reference the old binary name:\n- agents-managed.md.jinja: Protocol Quick Reference table has 'botbox protocol resume/start/review/finish/merge/cleanup', doc links use .agents/botbox/\n- docs/finish.md: references botbox protocol, .botbox.json, BOTBOX_PROJECT\n- docs/start.md: references botbox\n- docs/worker-loop.md: references botbox run worker-loop, .botbox.json\n- docs/merge-check.md: references botbox protocol merge, .botbox.json\n- docs/mission.md: references botbox run worker-loop\n- docs/preflight.md: references botbox-dev\n- reviewer.md.jinja, reviewer-security.md.jinja: reference botbox status, .agents/botbox/review-loop.md\nThese templates get synced to deployed projects on edict sync, so agents would get wrong CLI instructions until fixed.","kind":"task","title":"rename: embedded doc templates (botbox → edict)"}	blake3:7V3RSFlSPmDIkNunF_SE8uxgKd5Q9xYhNFk0TFKo0xw
1772643023026825	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwjwg		item.create	bn-1d30	{"description":"The pi_agent_rust Claude Code extension is embedded at src/templates/extensions/botbox-hooks.ts and run_agent.rs looks for it at ~/.pi/agent/extensions/botbox-hooks.ts.\n\nChanges needed:\n- Rename file to edict-hooks.ts (both in src/templates/extensions/ and target install path)\n- Update content: pi.exec('botbox', ...) → pi.exec('edict', ...), export default function botboxHooksExtension → edictHooksExtension, customType: 'botbox-hook' → 'edict-hook'\n- Update run_agent.rs: look for ~/.pi/agent/extensions/edict-hooks.ts","kind":"task","title":"rename: botbox-hooks.ts pi extension (name + content)"}	blake3:rSTapt73_dTrVLQpU-kTzIA7E9R5ZpT0AAQePFPENi4
1772643023205348	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwkAg		item.create	bn-3i2v	{"description":"Rename 'botbox' to 'edict' in all non-migrated string literals, error messages, log lines, and doc comments across src/. Key files with high counts: sync.rs (~49 refs), config.rs (~35), hooks.rs (~35), worker_loop.rs (~31), protocol/*.rs, run_agent.rs, doctor.rs, status.rs, telemetry.rs, etc.\n\nExcludes: CONFIG_TOML_LEGACY constant (intentionally keeps .botbox.toml string), migration function names/comments that explicitly reference the botbox-era for clarity, and test fixtures that test legacy behavior.","kind":"task","title":"rename: source code strings and comments (botbox → edict)"}	blake3:RRqiW9RDwrhY1jAqJgIfa63NAR6m-4uZVfyxYPHrbmk
1772643023384943	botbox-dev	itc:v3:AWLJPJJM5nmSc0AAAAAAQdXqrdvauwAAAAEwkQg		item.create	bn-2lu6	{"description":"Update ws/default/AGENTS.md and ws/default/CLAUDE.md which still describe the tool as 'botbox' throughout: ecosystem table, agent subcommand descriptions (botbox run dev-loop etc), hook commands (botbox hooks run), sync/init documentation, repo structure, release process, etc.\n\nNote: the managed section of AGENTS.md (between edict:managed-* markers) regenerates automatically on edict sync. The unmanaged section (the bulk of the file) must be updated manually.","kind":"task","title":"rename: this repo's AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md (botbox → edict)"}	blake3:D2x9zLeYxBxOS9xwJ_3w9b1MEQr3orXtrqqCUwLt7Mo
